  "author": "XO_OX Designs",
  "version": "1.0",
  "description": "THE holy grail preset. All four strata in full balance. Berimbau floor (gourd resonator + pitch sweep) feeds the canopy spectral filter and triggers bird calls. 14-second ecosystem drift LFO creates invisible population cycles — the preset never sounds the same twice. Canopy wavefold=0.42 for Buchla-style harmonic richness. Emergent→Canopy shimmer feedback means every bird call adds a shimmer tail that shapes the next call's formants via Canopy→Emergent formant route. A self-sustaining sonic ecosystem. One note, played long. The producer stops. They listen again. They leave the note running for three minutes before moving on.",
  "tags": [
    "holy-grail",
    "ecosystem",
    "self-sustaining",
    "berimbau",
    "shimmer",
    "feedback",
    "guru-bin"
  ],
